'''İrfan Can Kahveci''' (born 15 July 1995) is a Turkish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[Midfielder (association football)#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] or a [[Midfielder (association football)#Winger|winger]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Kasımpaşa S.K.|Kasımpaşa]], on loan from [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]], and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
He started playing football at Gençlerbirliği Football School at the age of 7.<ref name="TFF"/> After the years he spent at the football school, İrfan entered the Gençlerbirliği youth team by showing himself in the selections. He signed a professional contract with [[Gençlerbirliği S.K.|Gençlerbirliği]] during the [[Fuat Çapa]] period. On 27 April 2012, Kahveci played in the last 5 minutes of the match against [[Kayserispor]] for the first for the club in the [[Spor Toto Cup]] match.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kayserispor 0-3 Gençlerbirliği|url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageID=29&macId=106122|accessdate=26 November 2024|date=27 April 2012|language=Turkish}}</ref>

====Hacettepe (loan)====
In the 2013-2014 season, he loaned to [[Hacettepe S.K.|Hacettepe]], the satellite team of Gençlerbirliği, to gain experience. Kahveci, who scored 4 goals in 34 matches here and contributed to Hacettepe's promotion to the [[TFF Second League]] at the end of the 2013-2014 season.<ref name="TFF"/>

===Gençlerbirliği===
On 29 August 2014, Irfan Can made his [[Süper Lig]] debut for the first team against [[Rizespor]] during the [[2014–15 Super Lig|2014–15 season]]. On 9 November 2014, he scored his first league goal in the 63rd minute against [[Kasımpaşa Spor Kulübü|Kasımpaşa]]. He finished the season with 6 goals in 30 matches in league and cup competitions.

In his [[2015–16 Super Lig|second season]] with Gençlerbirliği he amassed 3 goals in 33 matches in all competitions.

===İstanbul Başakşehir===
On 26 December 2016, Kahveci signed a contract with [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]] until the end of 2021-22 season.<ref>{{cite news|title=İrfan Can Kahveci resume Başakşehir'de|trans-title=İrfan Can Kahveci officially in Başakşehir|url=http://www.sabah.com.tr/spor/futbol/2016/12/26/irfan-can-kahveci-resmen-basaksehirde|accessdate=7 January 2017|work=[[Sabah (newspaper)|Sabah]]|date=26 December 2016|language=Turkish}}</ref> On 14 January 2016, he made debut with the team against [[Kayserispor]] as a substitute, Başakşehir won the match 5-0.

On 19 September 2017, he made his continental debut against [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|Hoffenheim]] in a [[UEFA Europa League]] away match, they lost 3-1.

On 2 December 2020, he scored a hat-trick against [[RB Leipzig]] in the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]]. His team, however, lost the match 3–4.<ref>{{cite web |date=2 December 2020 |title=RB Leipzig vs. Istanbul Basaksehir score: German side wins seven-goal thriller |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/rb-leipzig-vs-istanbul-basaksehir-score-german-side-wins-seven-goal-thriller/ |access-date=2 December 2020 |website=[[CBS Sports]]}}</ref> It made him only the third player to score a hat-trick in a losing cause in the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]], after [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]] and [[Gareth Bale]].<ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2020|title=Champions League hat-tricks: the full lowdown|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0257-0e99f0d0d91b-eb0f4ba7a8f7-1000--champions-league-hat-tricks-the-full-lowdown/|access-date=18 December 2020|website=[[UEFA]]}}</ref>

===Fenerbahçe===
On 31 January 2021, [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] announced via [[Twitter]] that Kahveci joined the team.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=Fenerbahce |number=1355967502594043905 |title=Ailemize hoş geldin İrfan Can Kahveci |trans-title=Welcome to our family İrfan Can Kahveci |language=tr}}</ref> He signed a four-and-a-half-year contract with Fenerbahçe for a €7 million fee.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2021-tr/2/irfan-can-kahveci-fenerbahcemizde |title=İrfan Can Kahveci Fenerbahçemizde |date=31 January 2021 |website=Fenerbahçe SK |language=tr |access-date=31 January 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kap.org.tr/en/Bildirim/906610 |title=Futbolcu İrfan Can Kahveci'nin transferinin sonuçlanması hk |date=31 January 2021 |website=kap.org.tr |language=tr |access-date=31 January 2021}}</ref>

On 4 March 2021, he made his debut against [[Antalyaspor]] at the [[Şükrü Saracoğlu Stadium]], [[Süper Lig]] match tied 1–1.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2021-tr/3/fenerbahce-1-1-fta-antalyaspor | title=Fenerbahçe 1-1 FTA Antalyaspor |website=fenerbahce.org |date=4 March 2021 |language=tr |access-date=22 August 2023}}</ref> On 30 October 2021, he scored his first goal against [[Konyaspor]], Fenerbahçe lost 2–1.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2021-tr/10/ittifak-holding-konyaspor-2-1-fenerbahce | title=İttifak Holding Konyaspor 2-1 Fenerbahçe |website=Fenerbahçe SK |date=30 October 2021 |language=tr |access-date=22 August 2023}}</ref>

In [[2023–24 Fenerbahçe S.K. season|2023–24 season]], he made a very strong start with new coach and team's local legend [[İsmail Kartal]] and became one of the key players who took more responsibility on the field.<ref name="Sozcu" /> He scored 12 goals in 31 [[Süper Lig]] matches and 6 goals in 14 [[UEFA Conference League]] matches.

On 26 October 2023, he wore a Fenerbahçe jersey for the 100th time in all competitions against [[PFC Ludogorets Razgrad|Ludogorets Razgrad]] in [[2023–24 UEFA Europa Conference League|UEFA Europa Conference League Group H]] third week match, Fenerbahçe won 3–1 in [[Şükrü Saracoğlu Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2023/10/irfan-can-kahveci-fenerbahce-formasiyla-100-macina-cikti |title=İrfan Can Kahveci, Fenerbahçe formasıyla 100. maçına çıktı |date=26 October 2023 |website=Fenerbahçe SK |language=tr |access-date=26 October 2023}}</ref>

On 12 January 2025, Fenerbahçe announced that they had signed a three-year contract with Kahveci until June 2028.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/1/irfan-can-kahveci-3-yil-daha-fenerbahcemizde |title=İrfan Can Kahveci 3 yıl daha Fenerbahçemizde |website=Fenerbahçe SK |date=12 January 2025 |language=tr |access-date=27 January 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Kahveci was called up by manager [[Fatih Terim]] for [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]]'s friendly match against [[Russia national football team|Russia]] on 31 August 2016 and subsequent [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group I|World Cup 2018 qualifier]] against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]].<ref>{{cite news |date=26 August 2016 |title=Fatih Terim'den sürpriz kadro! |url=http://spor.haber7.com/milli-takim/haber/2095678-fatih-terimden-surpriz-kadro |access-date=29 August 2016 |publisher=Haber 7}}</ref> He made a debut in the national team on 23 March 2018 in a 1–0 win against [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Football MATCH: 23.03.2018 Turkey v Rep. of Ireland|url=https://eu-football.info/_match.php?id=15425|website=eu-football.info|access-date=24 March 2018|date=23 March 2018}}</ref> In his second match in June 2019, a friendly against Uzbekistan, he had a chance to score his first international goal, but he missed a 90th-minute penalty kick. Turkey still won the game 2–0 courtesy of a brace from [[Zeki Çelik]].

==Playing style==
In his early years at [[Gençlerbirliği S.K.|Gençlerbirliği]], he played as a left-back<ref name="TFF"/><ref>{{cite web |title=İrfan Can Kahveci "Gençlerbirliği'nin Yıldızını Avrupa'da Taşımak İsterim!" |url=https://www.klasspor.com/tr/haber/57531-Irfan_Can_Kahveci_Genclerbirliginin_yildizini_Avrupada_tasimak_isterim.html |access-date=28 July 2015 |website=Klas Spor}}</ref> position and then, his loan period at [[Hacettepe S.K.|Hacettepe]] and senior career with Gençlerbirliği, Kahveci was deployed in several positions, most notably as a [[deep-lying midfielder]] and a [[wide midfielder]] primarily on the right side as he was deemed too small to play in the middle of the park.<ref name="TFF">{{cite web |title=İrfan Can Kahveci: "Sporcu olmak için doğmuşum" |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=286&ftxtID=22216 |access-date=2 February 2015 |website=TFF.org}}</ref> After transfers to [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]] in the [[2016–17 İstanbul Başakşehir F.K. season|2016–17 season]], manager [[Abdullah Avcı]] inserted Kahveci into the [[playmaker]] role, where his vision, passing, technical skill and ability to read and understand the game suited him. Since that season, Kahveci was primarily deployed in the position or as a [[central attacking midfielder]] at both club and international level. The player personally said that playing central midfield was his preference.<ref>{{cite web |title=İrfan Can Kahveci: 8 numarada oynamaktan büyük keyif alıyorum |url=https://www.haberturk.com/irfan-can-kahveci-8-numarada-oynamaktan-buyuk-keyif-aliyorum-3644687-spor |access-date=13 December 2023 |website=HaberTürk}}</ref>

As a result of his versatility, Kahveci could also function on the wing and spent the majority of his career at [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]], occupying the role in the team's 4–3–3 formation.<ref>{{cite web |title=Fenerbahçe'nin yeni transferi İrfan Can Kahveci kimdir nereli kaç yaşında? İşte, mevkisi ve oynadığı takımlar |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/fenerbahcenin-yeni-transferi-irfan-can-kahveci-kimdir-nereli-kac-yasinda-iste-mevkisi-ve-oynadigi-takimlar-41729945 |access-date=1 February 2021 |website=Hürriyet}}</ref> His close control with the ball, speed, [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]], [[Cross (association football)|crossing]] and shots from outside the box, which resulted in former manager [[İsmail Kartal]] deploying Kahveci in the role during the player's situation at the club.<ref name="Sozcu">{{cite web|title=İrfan Can Kahveci'ye İsmail Kartal dokunuşu|url=https://www.sozcu.com.tr/irfan-can-kahveci-ye-ismail-kartal-dokunusu-p23885|website=Sözcü|access-date=20 February 2024}}</ref>

